{"id":"2008.07419","submitter":"Pedro Henrique Santos Bento","authors":"Pedro H. S. Bento, Marcel Novaes","title":"Semiclassical treatment of quantum chaotic transport with a tunnel\n  barrier","comments":"17 pages, 5 figures","journal-ref":"J. Phys. A: Math. Theor. 54 125201 (2021)","doi":"10.1088/1751-8121/abcf58","report-no":null,"categories":"nlin.CD cond-mat.mes-hall math-ph math.MP","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We consider the problem of a semiclassical description of quantum chaotic\ntransport, when a tunnel barrier is present in one of the leads. Using a\nsemiclassical approach formulated in terms of a matrix model, we obtain\ntransport moments as power series in the reflection probability of the barrier,\nwhose coefficients are rational functions of the number of open channels M. Our\nresults are therefore valid in the quantum regime and not only when $M\\gg 1$.\nThe expressions we arrive at are not identical with the corresponding\npredictions from random matrix theory, but are in fact much simpler. Both\ntheories agree as far as we can test.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 17 Aug 2020 15:44:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-07-06"}
